"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/945519","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-25","<p>The rights of a residential boat owner will depend on the terms of their agreement with the operator of the mooring. The Government has no plans to introduce legislation to regulate for security of tenure for residential houseboat owners.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-07-25T15:44:26.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/945519/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/945519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/945519/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-20","Houseboats: Security of Tenure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he has plans to bring forward legislative proposals for the regulation of security of tenure for residential boats.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","166492"
